# Build the Multi-Root Graph Projection

## Question

Extend the single-root `graph.json` (704 nodes, 145 edges — see [the closed bugle ticket](../bugle-redesign/build-wikilink-edges-graph-json.svx)) to the proof's three roots: dark-wizard user brain, `joelclaw` `.brain`, `joelclaw-wiki` `.brain`, read from flagg's local checkouts via the decided discovery mechanism.

- Every node carries root provenance: repo, path, commit at build time (acceptance item 4's data).
- Cross-root wikilink edges resolve under the decided namespace policy; unresolved and ambiguous links are first-class nodes/flags, not dropped.
- Schema version bumps; the no-invented-edges property tests extend to cross-root edges; two independent runs stay deterministic.
- Store-agnostic: graph.json remains the deterministic build artifact regardless of what the store research picks — a store ingests this projection, it doesn't replace it.

Data only — no UI. Executes in `joelhooks/joelclaw-wiki`. Resolved when the three-root graph.json builds from real data with tests, documented shape, and honest cross-root edge counts in the resolution.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Built by the multi-root pi worker (wJ:p4, 50 turns), independently verified and committed by the steering session (wiki repo `420067d`: 150/150 tests, svelte-check 0 errors, stats reproduced).

- **863 nodes / 161 edges** across the three registry roots — user 222/38, joelclaw 78/11, wiki 563/112. By kind: 309 brain pages, 496 observations, 23 open loops, 15 projects, 20 unresolved targets. Two real builds byte-identical.
- Schema v2: root provenance (root/repo/path/commit) on every node; lexical-scope resolution implemented per the namespace policy; ambiguity records first-class (0 today); privacy flags carried into node metadata for the rendering layer to gate.
- Audit works and earns its keep immediately: all 3 registered roots present, **17 unregistered `.brain` directories** reported loudly under `~/Code/joelhooks/` — the registry has real onboarding decisions waiting.
- **Cross-root edges: 0 — honest and expected.** No brain note anywhere used `[[root/slug]]` before today (the syntax was born this session), and no bare slug happens to resolve globally-unique across roots. Acceptance item 3 gets proven by the navigation prototype with organic cross-root links as they appear; nothing was manufactured to fake the number.
- Shape documented in `joelclaw-wiki/.brain/graph-shape.svx`; `wiki graph build|stats` operational.
- Unblocks the wiki-repo half of [Prototype Cross-Root Navigation](./prototype-cross-root-navigation.svx) — still gated by the rendering-model → privacy chain, by design.
